<TITLE> Speaker to consider SQ Chy's fate </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 17 (bdnews24.com)Speaker Abdul Hamid said Wednesday he would consider the Election Commission's letter on the issue of BNP MP Salahuddin Quader Chowdhury's seat in the House. "The letter has reached the parliament secretariat, but not to me," speaker Abdul Hamid told reporters in the afternoon. "I will examine it in time and give my opinion," he said. The EC sent the letter to the speaker seeking cancellation of Chowdhury's membership of the House for submitting false information in his nomination papers and defying a court order to rectify it. Election commissioner M Sakhawat Hussain said on Tuesday that the EC was of the opinion that the senior BNP leader should be disqualified as MP from Chittagong-2. Sakhawat referred to section 12 of the Representation of the People Order, which states an MP will lose membership if he provides false information in his affidavit to the EC, amounting to perjury. The speaker can take necessary steps according to parliamentary laws and the Member of Parliament (determination of dispute) Act 1980, said Sakhawat. The EC says Chowdhury provided the EC with false information about his educational qualifications. Challenging the EC, the MP told bdnews24.com on Tuesday that the commission must prove that he had lied or furnished 'untrue' information. Speaking to bdnews24.com by phone from Singapore, he claimed neither the commission nor the speaker had the power to strip him of the right to represent his electorate. He said he had not provided any false information about his credentials. On conflicting information about his SSC exams, Chowdhury said: "I didn't submit any biography to the commission. It might have been collected from the parliament secretariat. The BNP leader went to Singapore on Monday night for medical treatment
